# Copy to .sandcastle/.env.review and fill in. This file is gitignored, and is loaded ONLY
# into the host process — never into any agent sandbox. That is the whole point: the reviewer
# credential must not reach the implement/heal/resolve containers, or an agent could approve
# its own PR and the loop would merge it (#32).
#
# The loop injects this token into the REVIEW run alone. Required in internal review mode;
# unused in external mode.

# --- Forge identity: REVIEWER (review-agent, MUST be a different account than the implementer) ---
# Used by `forge ... --as-reviewer` so approvals aren't attributed to the author.
# GitHub: a fine-grained PAT (Contents RW, Pull requests RW, Issues RW, Metadata R) for a
#         second bot account that is a write collaborator.
# GitLab: a project/personal access token (api, write_repository) for the reviewer bot.
FORGE_REVIEW_TOKEN=
